===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|cotoun|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|cotun|lang=xno}}, from {{etyl|roa-oit}} (Genoa) {{term|cotone|lang=it}}, from {{etyl|ar}} (Egypt) {{term|قطن|sc=Arab|tr=qúţun|lang=ar}}, (Hispano-Arab) {{term||quṭūn}}, variants of {{etyl|ar}} {{term|قُطْن|sc=Arab|tr=quṭn|lang=ar}}, from root {{recons|qţn|lang=ar}}, possibly originally from Ancient Egyptian.

Cognate to Dutch {{term|katoen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Kattun|lang=de}}, Italian {{term|cotone|lang=it}}, Spanish {{term|algodón|lang=es}}, and Portuguese {{term|algodão|lang=pt}}.<ref name="oetyld">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

